===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈfæsɪt/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-facet.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|æsɪt|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Any one of the flat [[surface]]s cut into a gem.
#: ''This '''facet''' of the diamond was masterfully cut to enhance its value.''
# One among many [[similar]] or [[related]], yet still [[distinct]] things.
#: ''The child's learning disability was only one '''facet''' of the problems contributing to his delinquency.''
# One of a [[series]] of things, such as [[step]]s in a project.
#: ''We had just about completed the research '''facet''' of the project when the order came to cancel it''.
# {{lb|en|anatomy}} One member of a [[compound eye]], as found in [[insect]]s and [[crustacean]]s.
# {{lb|en|anatomy}} A smooth circumscribed surface.
#: ''the articular '''facet''' of a bone''
# {{lb|en|anatomy}} Any of the small [[joint]]s at each segment of the [[spine]] that provide stability and help guide motion
# {{lb|en|architecture}} The narrow [[plane]] [[surface]] between [[fluting]]s of a [[column]].
# {{lb|en|mathematics}} A [[face]] of [[codimension]] 1 of a [[polytope]].

